{#
  adopter-welcome.step-0.mjml — Day 1 welcome for a new FPG adopter.
  Source: SharePoint > AdoptionandEngagement > Adoption > Organizing Adopters
          > Drip Emails for adopter Sign-up.docx (Email 1).
#}
{% extends "_base.html.jinja" %}
{% block body %}
  <h2 style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#2C474B;font-size:18px">Welcome! You've Just Adopted a People Group</h2>
  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">Hi {{ contact_display_name }},</p>
  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">You've taken a bold and beautiful step.</p>
  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    By adopting a Frontier People Group, you've joined a growing movement of
    believers who long to see the Good News reach the ends of the earth,
    especially where it's never been heard.
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0 0 24px;color:#374151">
    Right now, you're standing in the gap for a community that likely has no
    access to Scripture, no nearby churches, and no known believers. This act
    of obedience and love matters more than you may ever know.
  </p>

  <h3 style="margin:0 0 12px;color:#2C474B;font-size:16px">What's Next</h3>
  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    Over the next few weeks, we'll guide you with helpful resources to pray,
    learn, and take further steps of action, all at your own pace. Whether
    you're praying by yourself, with your family, or considering how to
    mobilize your church, you're not in this alone.
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    The <a href="https://joshuaproject.net/adopt/files/jp-global-pga-manual-v3.pdf" style="color:#eb5f1e;text-decoration:underline"><em>Global Frontier People Group Adoption Manual</em></a> is here for your
    guidance. It is a stand-alone document that will serve to guide you
    through FPG adoption. This manual can be printed and used free of charge.
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0 0 24px;color:#374151">
    If you have chosen to collaborate with other adopters or organizations
    aimed at reaching the same FPG, we hope to match you with those who have
    committed to seeing them engaged with the Gospel in the months ahead.
    Matches will be made as they are available and only with those who have
    agreed to collaborate.
  </p>

  <h3 style="margin:0 0 12px;color:#2C474B;font-size:16px">Your Commitment</h3>
  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">
    Here you will find your Adoption Certificate. Please fill it in and post
    it somewhere that reminds you, and your group, of your commitment to
    seeing this FPG reached with the Gospel.
  </p>

  <p style="margin:0 0 16px;color:#374151">Thank you for saying yes. Eternity will look different because of it.</p>

  <p style="margin:0 0 8px;color:#374151">In hope,<br/>The Joshua Project Team</p>
  <p style="margin:0;color:#6b7280;font-style:italic;font-size:13px">"Let the nations be glad…" (Psalm 67:4 NIV)</p>
{% endblock %}
